en_213640_0	The United Nations Subcommittee on Prevention of Torture began their first visit to Sri Lanka today. the visit will end on the 12 th of April.
en_213640_1	The objective of the tour is to examine the treatment of people deprived of their liberty and the safeguards in place for their protection against torture and ill-treatment.
en_213640_2	The four-member delegation will meet Government officials and hold discussions with relevant Ministries, as well as meetings with the Human Rights Commission and civil society organisations.
en_213640_3	Their talks in Colombo will focus on advising and assisting the Sri Lankan authorities regarding the measures they must take to be in compliance with the obligations contained in the Optional Protocol to the UN Convention against Torture.
